- As the OPA passes through the oral cavity and approaches the posterior wall of the pharynx, rotate the device $180^{\circ}$ into the proper position (Figure 38C). You can also insert the OPA at a $90^{\circ}$ angle to the mouth and then turn it down toward the posterior pharynx as you advance the device.

