- Attach the monitor/defibrillator.

Once the monitor/defibrillator is attached, check the rhythm to determine whether it is shockable (VF/pVT) or nonshockable (asystole/PEA) and follow the appropriate cardiac arrest pathway.

\section*{Managing Asystole/PEA}

This patient has an organized rhythm on the monitor but no pulse. The condition is PEA (Step 9). Resume chest compressions immediately. The Team Leader now directs the team in the steps outlined in the asystole/PEA pathway of the Adult Cardiac Arrest Algorithm (Figure 49).
